Many people think that sports participants be paid too much for just playing sport they like. In my opinion, some people criticise playing sports at professional level is easy, but actually it’s not as easy as they think. The athletes sacrifice their health and spend their time at gym and practice to maintain physical performance.

First of all, professional athletes often sacrifice their health for their career. They train hard every day, which can cause serious injuries such as broken bones, muscle damage, or long-term pain. For example, many basketball players often continue playing despite ankle injuries or knee pain during important games. Some athletes continue competing even when they are injured because they don’t want to disappoint their team or fans. In addition, the pressure of competition can also affect their mental health. Therefore, athletes deserve high salaries because they risk both their physical and mental well-being.

Secondly, it’s extremely difficult to maintain top performance in sports. Athletes must follow strict schedules, including training, healthy diet, and regular practice. They cannot simply relax whenever they want because one small mistake can reduce their performance. For example,LeBron Raymone James is known for following a strict diet and daily training routine for many years to stay in top condition. Moreover, they need strong discipline and motivation to stay in shape for many years. Becoming a professional athlete requires not only talent, but also hard work and consistency.

In conclusion, although some people believe athletes are overpaid, being professional sports player is not easy at all. Athletes sacrifice their health and work incredibly hard to maintain their form and performance. For these reasons, they deserve the money.


2. Discussion : Some people think students should wear school uniforms, while others think they should choose their own clothes. Discuss both views.

Many people have different opinions about school uniforms. Some people think students should wear uniforms at school, while others believe students should be free to choose their own clothes. This essay will discuss both views.

On the one hand, some people think school uniforms are a good idea. Uniforms make students look equal and can reduce pressure about fashion or expensive brands. For example, I wear a school uniform myself, and I think it makes school easier because everyone looks similar and no one pays too much attention to clothing. I also do not need to spend time choosing clothes every morning, which saves time before school. Because of this, many students feel more comfortable in a school uniform.

On the other hand, some people think students should choose their own clothes. They believe clothes are a way to express personality and individual style. For example, even though I wear a school uniform at school, outside of school I enjoy choosing my own clothes because it feels more personal and comfortable. Different clothes can also affect mood and confidence. Because of this, many students prefer having more freedom to wear what they like instead of the same uniform every day.

In conclusion, some people support school uniforms because they create equality and make school life simpler. However, others believe students should choose their own clothes because it helps them express themselves and feel more confident. Both opinions have good reasons, and each school may decide differently depending on what is best for students.


3. Many students spend too much time on their phones. What problems does this cause, and what are some possible solutions?

Many students spend a lot of time on their phone every day. Phones are useful for communication and entertainment, but using them too much can create problems. This essay will discuss some problems caused by phone overuse and possible solutions.

One problem is that spending too much time on phones can affect students studies. Many students check social media, watch videos, or play games instead of doing homework. This can make it difficult to focus and manage time well. For example, I sometimes notice that when I use my phone too long, I lose track of time and finish my work later than as I planned. As a result, students may feel stressed or tired because they have less time for studying or sleeping.

There are several ways to solve this problem. One solution is setting time limits for phone use, specially while studying. Students can put their phone away or turn off notifications during homework time. For example, when I focus on one task without checking my phone, I can finish faster and with fewer distractions. Another solution is doing other activities such as sports, reading, or spending time with friends. This can help students use their free time in a healthier and more productive way.

In conclusion, spending too much time on phones can cause problems with studying, focus, and sleep. However these problems can reduced by setting limits and spending more time on other activities. With better habits student can enjoy phones without letting them control too much on their free time and full day.
